            <div class="space-y-4">
                <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold text-light-text dark:text-dark-text leading-tight">
                    Origin — Scarcity for Retail Finance
                </h1>
                
                <p class="text-lg text-light-muted dark:text-dark-muted max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
                    First principles for applying Scarcity to retail brokerage data.
                </p>
                
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <article class="bg-white dark:bg-dark-card/70 border border-light-border dark:border-dark-border rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 md:p-10">
            <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
                <p><strong>Question</strong></p>
<p>Retail brokerages have uneven traffic and strict privacy boundaries. Can a federated model learn a stable signal without relying on any single participant?</p>
<p><strong>Decision</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Use a simple FedAvg baseline with reliability-weighted updates (participation rate + recency).  </li>
<li>Start with synthetic clients that mimic real volume patterns before touching production data.  </li>
<li>Reserve a thin validation stream from one broker willing to share anonymized aggregates for evaluation only.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Failure (so far)</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Early simulations collapsed when a high-volume client went silent; the weighting scheme still over-trusted its last update.  </li>
<li>Communication overhead was higher than expected because payload compression was skipped for speed.  </li>
<li>Evaluation drifted because the validation stream did not represent weekend/holiday behavior.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Next uncertainty</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>How much personalization per brokerage is needed before the global model stops overreacting?  </li>
<li>What governance do partners need to trust the aggregation loop?  </li>
<li>Does a meta-learning warm start outperform fine-tuning given the participation gaps?</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Pointers</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Scarcity overview for the constraint model: <a href="/scarcity/overview">Scarcity System Overview</a>  </li>
<li>Primer on the paradigm: <a href="/library/learning-paradigms/federated-learning">Federated Learning Under Scarcity</a></li>
</ul>
            </div>
        </article>
        
        
    </div>
</section>

